### [Ephesians Chapter 4](../../../bib/kjv/eph004.htm#001.md)

[Ephesians 4:11](../../../bib/kjv/eph004.htm#011.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_011">eph 4:11</span></span>

gave

In ([Co1 12:8-28](../../../bib/kjv/co1012.htm#008).md), the Spirit is seen
as enduing the members of the body of Christ with spiritual gifts, or
enablements for a varied service; here, certain Spirit-endued men,
namely, apostles, prophets, evangelists, pastors, and teachers, are
themselves the gifts whom the glorified Christ bestows upon His body the
church. In Corinthians, the gifts are spiritual enablements for specific
service; in Ephesians, the gifts are men who have such enablements.

some

The Lord, in bestowing the gifted men, determines, providentially, (for
example); ([Act 11:22-26](../../../bib/kjv/act011.htm#022).md), or directly
through the Spirit, (for example); ([Act
13:1](../../../bib/kjv/act013.htm#001).md); ([Act
13:2](../../../bib/kjv/act013.htm#002).md); ([Rev
16:6](../../../bib/kjv/rev016.htm#006).md); ([Rev
16:7](../../../bib/kjv/rev016.htm#007).md) the places of their service.
"Some" (churches or places) ,need one gift, as, (for example);
evangelist; "some" (churches or places) need rather a pastor or teacher.
Absolutely nothing in Christ's service is left to mere human judgment or
self-choosing. Even an apostle was not permitted to choose his place of
service. ([Act 16:7](../../../bib/kjv/act016.htm#007).md); ([Act
16:8](../../../bib/kjv/act016.htm#008).md).

